<HEADLINE> State trooper injured in multi-vehicle crash on Interstate 80  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROCKAWAY, N.J. (AP) - A state trooper and two other people were
injured Tuesday night in a five-vehicle crash on Interstate 80,
according to the State Police.
</P>
<P>
   The trooper, identified as E. Schnezler from the Netcong
barracks, suffered a head laceration in the 7:30 p.m. crash. He was
taken to Morristown Memorial Hospital and was expected to remain
there overnight, the State Police said.
</P>
<P>
   Kathy Burwell, the nursing supervisor at the hospital, said the
trooper was listed in stable condition.
</P>
<P>
   Schnezler was westbound on I-80 at the time of the crash. A
State Police spokesman said Schnezler was stopped in traffic when
his patrol car was struck from behind by another vehicle.
</P>
<P>
   Two other people were taken to local hospitals, the spokesman
said. Joann Medina, 43, of Hazleton, Pa., had neck and back pains,
and Laszlo Ponisak, 58, of Bryan, Ohio, suffered chest pains.
</P>
<P>
   The cause of the accident remains under investigation. The crash
snarled traffic on the road for several hours.
</P>
</TEXT>
