<HEADLINE> Man Admits Stalking Brooke Shields  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A New Jersey accountant admitted in court
that he stalked actress Brooke Shields and made terrorist threats
against her, then entered a plea of no contest.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Bailey, 41, was ordered Tuesday to leave California and
return to his home state, where he will remain on probation for
five years. He had already served nearly a year in jail.
</P>
<P>
   He also was ordered to undergo psychiatric counseling twice a
week, to take medication as prescribed by his doctor and to report
to a probation officer.
</P>
<P>
   ''You must not harass or molest the victim or threaten use of
force or violence against anyone,'' Superior Court Judge Maureen
Duffy-Lewis told him.
</P>
<P>
   She told Bailey he may not have contact with Shields, her
agents, family or representatives for 10 years. Shields has said
Bailey harassed her for 15 years -- sending her nude photos of
himself and letters threatening her with harm.
</P>
<P>
   Shields, who did not attend Tuesday's hearing, submitted a
statement which was read in court expressing her gratitude to the
district attorney's office and saying, ''I believe that no one in
our society should have to live in constant terror and fear.''
</P>
</TEXT>
