<HEADLINE> 5 Hurt at Mexican Transformer Fires  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY (AP) -- Ten transformers caught fire at a
hydroelectric plant outside Mexico City, injuring five workers, the
Federal Electrical Commission said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The fire in the Tingambato plant late Tuesday trapped five
maintenance workers, but two were rescued and three were able to
escape, officials said in a news release. All were in good
condition. Earlier media reports had said three dozen people were
injured, but a spokesman denied that Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The blaze did not affect electrical service in Mexico. Officials
said they would start an investigation to determine the fire's
cause.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
