<HEADLINE> 'E.T.' To Be Re-Released  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNIVERSAL CITY, Calif. (AP) -- ''E.T.'' will be phoning home
again.
</P>
<P>
   The 20th anniversary of Steven Spielberg's blockbuster ''E.T.
The Extraterrestrial'' will be celebrated with a theater re-release
that includes computer-generated enhancements and never-before-seen
footage.
</P>
<P>
   Universal Pictures and Amblin Entertainment said the 1982
heart-warmer will be back in theaters in March 2002.
</P>
<P>
   ''I always wanted to give audiences another chance to experience
it as they first did -- in theaters, seeing it again, or seeing it
with their families,'' Spielberg said. ''I also wanted to enhance
that experience with advances in technology.''
</P>
<P>
   ''E.T.'' has grossed about $700 million at the box office.
</P>
