<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-06 16:07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Daryl Hannah To Make Stage Debut  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Daryl Hannah has been in more than 30 movies. But
a bad case of stage fright has kept her from doing theater.
</P>
<P>
   That will change next month, when she makes her professional
stage debut in ''The Seven Year Itch.''
</P>
<P>
   ''I have this big thing with stage fright, and it's always been
an issue,'' Hannah, 39, said Wednesday. ''So I figure it's now or
never.''
</P>
<P>
   Hannah is cast in the revival of George Axelrod's play as The
Girl -- the role played by Marilyn Monroe in the 1955 film.
</P>
<P>
   The play opens Oct. 9 at London's Queen's Theater.
</P>
<P>
   Hannah, whose films have included ''Splash'' and ''Roxanne,''
she wasn't interested in doing a ''shabby impersonation'' of
Monroe.
</P>
<P>
   Far more pressing, she said, is overcoming her nerves.
</P>
<P>
   ''Either I'll survive it, or I won't,'' she said.
</P>
</TEXT>
