<HEADLINE> Time Warner Ad Rankles N.J. Governor  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TRENTON, N.J. (AP) -- A Time Warner Cable ad touting a new
picture-in-picture service that is so easy ''even somebody from
Jersey can use it'' has rankled Gov. Christie Whitman.
</P>
<P>
   Whitman fired off a letter to the president of the cable company
Wednesday, saying the mailed ad was offensive to New Jersey
residents and ignored the state's many technological advances.
</P>
