<HEADLINE> Saints' Williams Questionable  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- New Orleans running back Ricky Williams was a
surprise addition to the team's injury list on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Williams woke up with a swollen right foot Monday morning and it
was placed in a walking cast. He doesn't remember injuring it but
it was swollen and he was hobbled by it Monday and Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''He could barely walk,'' coach Jim Haslett said Wednesday. ''We
planned to hold him out of practice, but I looked up and he was in
there.''
</P>
<P>
   Williams said he had planned to work the entire practice
Wednesday. When the team ran sprints at the end of practice, he
rode an exercise bike for about 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   X-rays were negative and he was diagnosed with a bruised foot.
</P>
<P>
   Williams was listed as questionable on the injury report for
Sunday's game at San Diego, but Haslett said unless the foot reacts
badly to the work Wednesday, he'll be upgraded to probable
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   ''If I'm practicing on Wednesday, then everything should be fine
on Sunday,'' Williams said.
</P>
