<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-06 20:21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Giants Offense Faces Test Vs Eagles  </HEADLINE>
By TOM CANAVAN
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- The New York Giants' offensive line
had an impressive debut against Arizona, opening holes for Tiki
Barber and Ron Dayne and not letting anyone lay a hand on
quarterback Kerry Collins.
</P>
<P>
   Now the linemen need to do it against Philadelphia's
blitz-happy, aggressive defense, which sent Troy Aikman to the
hospital in the Eagles' season-opening 41-14 win over the Dallas
Cowboys.
</P>
<P>
   Philadelphia held the Cowboys to 167 total yards, limiting
Emmitt Smith to 29 yards on seven carries. Aikman suffered the
ninth concussion of his 12-year career in a game where he was
sacked four times in just over a quarter.
</P>
<P>
   ''They dominated the line of scrimmage down there,'' Giants left
guard Glenn Parker said. ''That set the whole tone for the entire
game. So that's our challenge. We have to establish something, take
at least half the line of scrimmage and get our guys running.''
</P>
<P>
   The Giants' offensive line did more than that in the season
opener against the undermanned Cardinals.
</P>
<P>
   Barber rushed for 144 yards and two touchdowns, Dayne added 78
yards and a TD, and Collins wasn't sacked in hitting 17 of 25
passes for 172 yards in a 21-16 victory.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't care if you are playing the greatest team in the world
or the worst, you have to have your assignments right and we did
that,'' Parker said. ''That gives us confidence.''
</P>
<P>
   The offensive line was revamped in the offseason.
</P>
<P>
   The only player in the same spot as last year is right guard Ron
Stone.
</P>
<P>
   Right tackle Luke Petitgout was a failure at left guard as a
rookie, but the 1999 first-round draft pick has played well at
tackle. Parker, left tackle Lomas Brown and center Dusty Zeigler
were all signed as free agents in the offseason.
</P>
<P>
   Zeigler said one of the things that got the line going was
getting to know one another off the field.
</P>
<P>
   ''When practice was over we got together and blended
personalities,'' Zeigler said. ''It made everyone more comfortable
with one another. It probably broke the ice. Once you know what
kind of person they are, you expect certain things from them on the
football field.''
</P>
<P>
   Most of the Giants also know what to expect from the Eagles.
</P>
<P>
   ''It looks like the Eagles are back to some smash-mouth
defense,'' Barber said. ''We watched that tape and they are pretty
tough.''
</P>
<P>
   Not only do the Eagles have a good front four, they have three
very athletic linebackers, two outstanding corners in Troy Vincent
and Bobby Taylor, and a big hitter at safety in Brian Dawkins.
</P>
<P>
   Barber thinks the Giants' offense will do well against the
Eagles.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm not surprised by our success,'' he said. ''We put in a
month and a half of work after our minicamp where we all hunkered
down and learned this thing. It is paying off for us.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
