Dow Climbs 50, Nasdaq Down 130
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Tech stocks fell for a second straight session today as
analysts cut their ratings on several high-profile companies, while Blue chips
moved higher on news of a major deal in the financial services industry. The Dow
Jones industrial average closed up 50.03 at 11,310.64. The Nasdaq was down
129.84 at 4,013.34.
</P>
