2nd Athlete Kicked off Canada Team
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   TORONTO (AP) -- A second athlete in as many days has been kicked off the
Canadian Olympic team following a positive drug test. A director for the
Canadian Centre for Ethics in Sport said today that equestrian rider Eric Lamaze
has tested positive for cocaine. Yesterday, hammer thrower Robin Lyons was
removed from the team after testing positive for an anabolic steroid.
AP NewsBrief by GRETCHEN SCHWARTZ 
