<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-06 21:30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FSU's Williams Sidelined  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Starting offensive tackle Brett
Williams could miss Florida State's game against Georgia Tech on
Saturday because of a severely sprained left ankle.
</P>
<P>
   Williams has been trying to play despite the injury, which
occurred during the first week of two-a-day practices in August. An
MRI of the ankle confirmed Williams' ligaments are swollen.
</P>
<P>
   The sophomore left in the second quarter of the second-ranked
Seminoles' 29-3 victory over Brigham Young on Aug. 26, after
experiencing pain in his leg. But says he's confident that he will
be back in the lineup.
</P>
<P>
   ''(The ankle) should bother me all year, pain wise, but I'll get
better to where the pain doesn't bother me, and I can play,''
Williams said.
</P>
<P>
   Charron Dorsey, a 6-foot-7, 325-pound tackle, is expected to
fill in for Williams. It would be the senior's first career start
at offensive tackle.
</P>
<P>
   ''If I had a choice, I'd probably redshirt to make me better,''
Dorsey said. ''Coaches felt players were getting tired, so I'm an
extra body to help the guys out.''
</P>
<P>
   Williams said he would play Saturday should an offensive lineman
get injured. He is listed as questionable.
</P>
<P>
   As a freshman last season, Williams earned second-team
All-Atlantic Coast Conference honors as the Seminoles won the
national championship. He started the final seven games of the
season in place of the injured Ross Brannon.
</P>
</TEXT>
