<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-06 22:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BC-NY--UN Summit-Protests, 1st Ld-Writethru,590  </HEADLINE>
By LUKAS I. ALPERT
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP)- Honking horns mingled with voices of political
protest outside the walls of the United Nations on New York's
gridlocked streets Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   As the Millennium Summit began, demonstrators had their say on
everything from Middle East peace and slavery in Sudan to Cuban
leader Fidel Castro's presence and China's human rights policies.
</P>
<P>
   Nearby, shopowners cooled their heels behind police barricades,
cut off from customers by tight security measures.
</P>
<P>
   ''You lose some business, but on the other hand you pick up with
the foreigners coming in to buy converters and adapters,'' said Bob
Kramer, co-owner of Kramer's Hardware, which was frequently blocked
by motorcades passing along Second Avenue and 49th Street.
</P>
<P>
   Twenty-two protests were officially registered with police
Wednesday, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Thousands of Falun Gong practitioners from around the world
gathered in the morning at a park opposite the Chinese Mission to
protest a crackdown on the movement's followers that began last
year in China.
</P>
<P>
   After sitting, stock still, in silent meditative protest, and
listening to statements read by practitioners who said they had
been detained and beaten in China for practicing Falun Gong, the
group rose in unison and marched in orderly rows the 12 blocks to
the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
   Falun Gong has attracted millions of followers with its
philosophy of exercise, meditation and beliefs drawn from Buddhism,
Taoism and the unorthodox ideas of its founder Li Hongzhi. While
followers say Falun Gong promotes health and morality, China's
government has banned it as a cult.
</P>
<P>
   ''We practice three principles - truth, compassion, and
forbearance,'' said Dong Li, a computer programmer from Mamaroneck,
who has practiced Falun Gong for a year. ''This apparently is not
concordant with Communist doctrine,''
</P>
<P>
   ''We really hope that (Chinese President) Jiang Zemin will stop
persecuting people who want to do this. We have no other intentions
than peaceful ones,'' Dong said.
</P>
<P>
   The march brought the Falun Gong protesters past the Sudanese
Mission on Third Avenue, where a group of 60 protesters demanded
the arrest of Sudanese President Omar el-Bashir. Two of the
protesters, former slaves from Sudan and Mauritania, said the
United States is doing nothing to stop enslavement.
</P>
<P>
   ''Why should the president of a slaving nation be allowed to
walk free on the streets of New York?'' asked Charles Jacobs,
president of the American Anti-Slavery Group, a Boston-based
organization that tries to raise awareness of forced labor around
the world.
</P>
<P>
   Upon arriving at the United Nations, Falun Gong followers
silently hunkered down into the lotus position and began
meditating, while raucous neighbors nearby on Dag Hammerskjold
Plaza protested Iraqi President Saddam Hussein and Israeli Prime
Minister Ehud Barak.
</P>
<P>
   Later, they were all replaced by a new shift of demonstrators -
Iranians, sandwiched between Bangladeshis and anti-Castro Cubans.
</P>
<P>
   ''It is an insult to the free world that this man (Castro) is
here while the Dalai Lama was not allowed to attend,'' said Yvonne
Conde, a Cuban-American writer who lives in New York.
</P>
<P>
   Later, about a dozen sympathizers of the Iranian National
Council of Resistance, a Paris-based group that considers itself
Iran's government in exile, sat in the middle of First Avenue near
the U.N., screaming that Iranian President Mohammad Khatami is a
terrorist. Police arrived shortly and arrested them.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-09-06-00 2226 </TRAILER>
