<HEADLINE> Braves 7, Diamondbacks 1  </HEADLINE>
By GEORGE HENRY
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA (AP) -- Chipper Jones had two run-scoring singles and
Kevin Millwood gave up four hits in eight innings to lead the
Atlanta Braves past the slumping Arizona Diamondbacks 7-1 Wednesday
night.
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta, which has won three of four, increased their NL East
lead to two games over the second-place New York Mets, who lost
11-8 at Cincinnati.
</P>
<P>
   Arizona, which entered Wednesday six games behind NL
West-leading San Francisco, has lost four of five. Armando Reynoso
(10-10) lost his third straight start and dropped to 0-9 against
the Braves, giving up three runs and four hits in seven innings.
</P>
<P>
   The crowd of 25,529 was the smallest at Turner Field, which
opened in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Pitching in a cold drizzle, Millwood (9-10) retired 14 straight
after giving up a leadoff double to Greg Colbrunn in the fourth.
The Diamondbacks finally got a runner on Tony Womack's double in
the eighth.
</P>
<P>
   Millwood benefited from a great play by Rafael Furcal that ended
the inning. The pitcher was knocked down by Jay Bell's liner, but
the ball deflected to Furcal at shortstop and he threw to first.
</P>
<P>
   Millwood, who won for only the second time in seven starts since
Aug. 1, struck out seven and walked none in his longest outing of
the season. Terry Mulholland finished with a hitless ninth.
</P>
<P>
   Colbrunn doubled in Tony Womack with two outs in the first, but
Atlanta tied it in the fourth when B.J. Surhoff singled home a run
after fouling off five pitches.
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta took a 3-1 lead n the sixth. Furcal led off with a
double and was nearly thrown out trying to dive back to second when
third baseman Matt Williams fielded Andruw Jones' grounder.
Second-base umpire Eric Cooper, though, ruled that Furcal beat
Bell's tag.
</P>
<P>
   Chipper Jones doubled in Furcal, moving Andruw Jones to third
and Andres Galarraga followed with a run-scoring, double-play
grounder.
</P>
<P>
   Andruw Jones and Chipper Jones hit RBI singles off off
Byung-Hyun Kim in a four-run eighth that included a run-scoring
grounder by Galarraga off Mike Morgan and Javy Lopez's RBI single.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Millwood won his ninth game last year on June 28 after
making his 16th start. He finished the season 18-7. ... Millwood
made his 31st start Wednesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
