<HEADLINE> Wizards 1, Revolution 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FOXBORO, Mass. (AP) -- Miklos Molnar's goal five minutes into the
second half gave the Kansas City Wizards a 1-0 victory over the New
England Revolution on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Despite the defeat, New England was assured a playoff berth when
Columbus lost 3-1 to Chicago later Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Kansas City goalkeeper Tony Meola recorded his 16th shutout of
the season, adding to his own league record.
</P>
<P>
   Meola secured the victory with a minute left, making a kick-save
to block Mauricio Wright's header off a free kick by John Harkes.
Meola made two other late saves. A diving header by Beasley off
Wolde Harris' cross forced Meola to reach for the save in the 77th
minute. The goalkeeper punched away William Sunsing's 16-yard shot
three minutes later.
</P>
<P>
   The Revolution (12-13-6) didn't get its first shot on goal until
the 57th minute, when substitute Jamar Beasley forced Meola to make
a save near the left post.
</P>
<P>
   The game's lone goal came when Francisco Gomez slid a pass on
the left side to Chris Henderson, who made a run toward the New
England area before passing to Molnar. The Dane shot the ball in
from 2 yards away, near the right post.
</P>
<P>
   Henderson had hit the crossbar with a shot early in the game.
</P>
<P>
   Kansas City improved to an MLS-best 16-7-8.
</P>
</TEXT>
