<HEADLINE> Man hits his lawyer in court  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) - A lawyer was injured Wednesday when his
client punched him during a probation violation hearing in Monroe
County Court, deputies said.
</P>
<P>
   Assistant Public Defender David A. Duguay was cut in his chin
while trying to calm Douglas Tabon after Tabon threw a pen at a
witness during a probation violation hearing, court deputies said.
</P>
<P>
   Tabon, 22, a patient at Rochester Psychiatric Center, wasn't
charged because Duguay refused to press charges. Duguay couldn't be
reached for comment.
</P>
<P>
   Tabon was sentenced to five years probation July 7 after
pleading guilty to possessing a forged check.
</P>
<P>
   He allegedly violated probation three days after his sentencing
by punching an aide at the psychiatric center.
</P>
<P>
   A center employee was testifying when Tabon, who is in a
wheelchair, threw a pen at the witness, then rose partly from his
wheelchair and hit Duguay, deputies said.
</P>
