<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Father Accused in Fatal Fire  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MADISONVILLE, Texas (AP) -- A man charged with sexually
assaulting one of his stepdaughters forced their grandmother at
gunpoint to douse their trailer home with gasoline before it was
set on fire Wednesday. The stepdaughters and his own daughter were
killed.
</P>
<P>
   Rafael Holiday, 21, was jailed on three capital murder charges
in lieu of a $750,000 bond, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Tela Mange, a spokeswoman for the Department of Public Safety,
said how the fire began was still being investigated.
</P>
<P>
   The youngsters were 18 months old, 5 and 7. The youngest was
Holiday's.
</P>
<P>
   The children's mother had left to call 911 and returned to find
her home in flames, Mange said. The grandmother escaped through a
window.
</P>
<P>
   Holiday was indicted in April for aggravated sexual assault of
one of his stepdaughters, according to the Madison County District
Attorney's Office.
</P>
<P>
   He was free on $10,000 bond while awaiting trial, and a
protective order barring any contact with his wife and the girls
was in place, Mange said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
